## 31.08.25 â€“ TrueNAS and Windows VM
- Created a TrueNAS VM in Proxmox (4 vCPU, 16 GB RAM, 32 GB system disk).  
- Passed through the two new 8 TB drives â†’ created a **ZFS Mirror pool** (~7.14 TiB usable).  
- Created datasets: `Files`, `Photos`, `Videos`.  
- Set up SMB shares and tested access from Windows with a new user.  
- Created a **â€œdailyâ€ user with read-only rights** to avoid always using the admin account. This improves security by limiting potential damage if credentials are compromised.  
- Changed from DHCP to **static IP (192.168.xx.xx)** and set a DHCP reservation in the router.  
- Also created a Windows VM (no active use case yet).  
âœ… **Result:** NAS setup functional, shares accessible across devices on the network.  
ğŸ’¡ **Learning:** Important to use datasets instead of sharing the pool root. Gained experience with ACL and permissions management in TrueNAS.  

